            <title>[LU-420] Got dependency warning when install RHEL6 i686 build</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-420</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Got the following warning when try to install the latest lustre-master build #174 RHEL6/i686.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some of the packages you have selected for install are&lt;br/&gt;
missing dependencies.  You can exit the installation, &lt;br/&gt;
go back and change your package selections, or continue &lt;br/&gt;
installing these packages without their dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;rubygem-bunny-0.6.0-1.el6.noarch requires ruby(rubygems)&lt;br/&gt;
rubygem-mixlib-config-1.1.2-1.el6.noarch requires rubygems    &lt;br/&gt;
rubygem-uuidtools-2.1.1-1.el6.noarch requires ruby(rubygems)&lt;br/&gt;
rubygem-moneta-0.6.0-1.el6.noarch requires ruby(rubygems) &lt;br/&gt;
rubygem-ohai-0.5.8-1.el6.noarch requires rubygems  &lt;br/&gt;
rubygem-mixlib-cli-1.2.0-1.el6.noarch requires rubygems&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
